  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n\n2. Financial Penalties:\n- Fines can reach $500,000 or twice the value of the laundered funds\n- Civil monetary penalties may also apply\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Potential loss of professional licenses\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, criminal intent, and prior criminal history. Prosecution typically occurs under statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.\n\nI want to be clear that this is general legal information, not specific legal advice. For detailed guidance about a specific situation, consulting a qualified attorney is recommended.",
